Sure, here are a few more Japanese artists that have similar music styles to Hitomi:

1. Yuiko Ohara - a singer-songwriter known for creating gentle and introspective alternative pop music.

2. Yoriko - a solo artist known for creating ethereal pop songs with electronic and classical influences.

3. Ayase - a pop singer-songwriter influenced by jazz, soul, and R&B music.

4. Superfly - a Japanese rock band that blends rock and pop music with soul and funk influences.

5. Sakanaction - an electro rock band known for creating music that merges electronic dance music with rock and pop elements.

I hope you enjoy exploring these artists and discovering new Japanese music!
